This paper is about Bayesian deep learning models and their uncertainty estimates, which are commonly used in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The paper specifically focuses on dropout variational inference and alpha-divergences as alternative divergences to VI's KL objective. These topics are closely related to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), and systems and control (cs.SY). Therefore, these are the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper.
